				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{Does}=\frac{\mathrm{Clearance}\left(\mathrm{per}\ \mathrm{day}\right)\times \mathrm{factor}\times {\mathrm{MIC}}_{90}}{\mathrm{fu}\times \mathrm{F}}\div \left(1/\mathrm{conversion}\ \mathrm{rate}\right) $$\end{document}Does=Clearanceperday×factor×MIC90fu×F÷1/conversion ratePlasma clearance is expressed in L/day. The factor is the dividing AUC/MIC by 24 h. MIC90 is the 90th percentile of MIC distribution. fu is the free (unbound) fraction. F is the absolute bioavailability. The clearance、fu、F and conversion rates were cited from the previous studies [21, 22].
